techmeme.title: A look at Cybathlon, an event by ETH Zurich where researchers team up with people with disabilities in a competition to test brain-computer interfaces (Oliver Whang/New York Times)
Sources: Alibaba is renaming its AI app Tongyi to "Qwen", aiming to make it more like ChatGPT, and adding agentic-AI shopping features for platforms like Taobao (Luz Ding/Bloomberg)
Baidu unveils two AI chips: the M100 for efficient MoE inference, launching in 2026, and the M300 for training super-large multimodal models, coming in 2027 (Ben Jiang/South China Morning Post)
Attentive.ai, maker of Beam AI for automating preconstruction workflows using AI, raised $30.5M Series B led by Insight Partners, bringing total raised to $48M (Amit Chowdhry/Pulse 2.0)
Polymarket starts live testing its US exchange, first with select users, and says the exchange is fully functional with some users betting on real contracts (Denitsa Tsekova/Bloomberg)
